Mechanical Engineer - KIMECH-UAE
03 May 2014 09:34 PM - UAE
Job Reference: KIMECH - UAE Mechanical Engineer - Pumping Stations Location: United Arab EmiratesSalary: US$7000 - US$10000 per month + Expat PackageJob Type: PermanentIndustry: EngineeringInternational consulting engineer is seeking an experienced Mechanical Engineer with a background in water to join them on a pumping station project in the UAE.Required Experience:* Degree minimum in Mechanical Engineering* Chartered/ Professional Engineer from a recognised professional body or equivalent preferred* Minimum of 10 years' experience on large water projects involving infrastructural design including Utilities, with knowledge of codes, design manuals and construction practices.* Construction and site supervision experience.* Ability to manage and coordinate water construction project.* Senior management experience of large and complex utility projects.* Experienced in water supply and treatment plants, pumping stations, reservoirs, tanks and piping works.* Ability to interpret complex contract documents including plans, specifications, shop drawings.* Ability to make decisions and recommendations on significant engineering problems, and review drawings, specifications and installations for constructability.At the core of ewi is specialist international recruitment expertise. We have over 30 years' experience search and selection for key professionals, internationally. What sets us apart is a global approach: where larger recruitment firms may focus on local offices that give them a narrow, local view, ewi takes a global perspective. We look right across the world to get the talent and the opportunities our clients and candidates need.Should you meet all the requirements for this particular role then please contact Kirk Wilson at ewi or alternatively please send an up to date copy of your CV to (more...)
